Package: leastcostpath
Title: leastcostpath: Calculation of Least Cost Paths to model human movement across a landscape
Version: 0.1.4
Date: 2019-03-19
Authors@R: person("Joseph", "Lewis", email = "josephlewis1992@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Joseph Lewis <josephlewis1992@gmail.com>
URL: josephlewis.github.io
Description: R Implementation of Least Cost Path analysis. Provides functionality for slope, traversing slope, and  openness  cost surface calculation to be used when calculating individual Least Cost Path(s) or network.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: gdistance (>= 1.2-2), raster (>= 2.6-7), rgdal (>= 1.3-3), rgeos (>= 0.3-28), sp (>= 1.3-1), spdep (>= 0.7-4)
